description.p:
More specifically, in the example embodiment, goal management system 10 imposes the following rules regarding goals:



    

1. every goal is either a team goal, a team-related goal, or a personal goal;

2. every goal has an owner;

3. each team goal is linked to one team and is created and managed by the owner of that team;

4. each team goal except for team goals of the top team (i.e., each child goal) has a parent goal, and that parent goal is linked to the parent team of the team that is linked to the child goal;

5. each team goal except for team goals of the top team (i.e., each child goal) has an owner, and that owner is one of the other members of the parent team of the team that is linked to that child goal;

6. each team-related goal is linked to one team goal;

7. each team-related goal is owned by one of the other members of the team associated with the team goal to which the team-related goal is linked; and

8. personal goals are not linked to any other goals.


In addition, the owner of a goal is preferably the person who creates and manages that goal.

claim.claim-text:
1. A method of facilitating a guidance process of maintaining goals in a system with at least first and second goal types so as to promote goal alignment, the method comprising:
performing in a computer system by one or more processors of the computer system:
verifying alignment between a goal of a first type and a goal of a second type;
indicating alignment of the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type after a verification of alignment between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type;
determining, with the computer system, if the goal of the first type has been modified; and
when a goal of the first type is modified, executing goal alignment code to:
(i) check for alignment between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type in accordance with at least a rule for relationships between goals of the first goal type and goals of the second goal type;
(ii) provide alignment warning data for generation of an alignment warning display to alert a viewer of the display of an alignment warning between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type; and
(iii) generate a notice regarding alignment between the modified primary goal and the secondary goal.

4. The method of claim 3 further comprising:
providing data to the client computer system to display the wizard in response to a request from a user of the client computer system to modify the goal of the second type;
providing data to the client computer system to prompt the user to select a team to be associated with the goal of the second type from a drop-down list of teams;
receiving a selection by the user of the team;
providing data to the client computer system to prompt the user to select a parent goal for the goal of the second type from a list showing all team goals linked to the selected team wherein the parent goal selected by the user becomes the goal of the first type; and
receiving the selection of the goal.

15. An apparatus comprising:
a processor;
a memory, coupled to the processor, having code stored therein and executable by the processor to:
verify alignment between a goal of a first type and a goal of a second type;
indicate alignment of the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type after a verification of alignment between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type;
determine, with the computer system, if the goal of the first type has been modified; and
when a goal of the first type is modified, executing goal alignment code to:
(i) check for alignment between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type in accordance with at least a rule for relationships between goals of the first goal type and goals of the second goal type;
(ii) provide alignment warning data for generation of an alignment warning display to alert a viewer of the display of an alignment warning between the goal of the first type and the goal of the second type; and
(iii) generate a notice regarding alignment between the modified primary goal and the secondary goal.

18. The apparatus of claim 17 further comprising:
providing data to the client computer system to display the wizard in response to a request from a user of the client computer system to modify the goal of the second type;
providing data to the client computer system to prompt the user to select a team to be associated with the goal of the second type from a drop-down list of teams;
receiving a selection by the user of the team;
providing data to the client computer system to prompt the user to select a parent goal for the goal of the second type from a list showing all team goals linked to the selected team wherein the parent goal selected by the user becomes the goal of the first type; and
receiving the selection of the goal.
